R: @jeffposnick 
CC: @josephliccini 

Fixes #2073 

This adds support for a new, optional field in `PrecacheEntry` called `integrity`. If provided, it should be a value that conforms to the [subresource integrity](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Subresource_Integrity#Using_Subresource_Integrity) format, and it will be passed as-is as part of the the `RequestInit` when creating the `Request` used to populate the precache.

Actually generating the `integrity` fields is left as an exercise to the developer (at least for the time being—we *might* want to add in the ability to have the build tools generate them at some point in a future release).

The most likely way that developers would add them in is via a custom `manifestTransform` function that can operate on each entry and optionally add `integrity` properties to those that need them, like so:

```
const integrityManifestTransform = (originalManifest) => {
  const warnings = [];
  const manifest = originalManifest.map((entry) => {
    // If some criteria match:
    if (entry.url.startsWith('...')) {
      // This has to be a synchronous function call:
      entry.integrity = generateSRIInfo(entry.url);

      // Push a message to warnings if needed.
    }
    return entry;
  });

  return {warnings, manifest};
};
```

